@Comment:	Chi is not a very strong reader , but she gets by. She reads one word at a time , following with her finger. Mot gives her cues and hints or something , but I'm not sure exactly what her strategy is because Mot is hard to hear on the tape. Chi asks Mot to find the leaf as she reads. Did Mot ask this in BR1 , 2 , 3? It appears that Chi uses contextual cues to boost her reading. For example , she has no trouble reading the days of the week , but pauses before less predictable words in the text. Near the end of the book it is very likely that Mot is telling Chi what many of the words are , but only Chi is heard on the tape.
